'''Nokia Software Updater''' is a [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] based application from [[Nokia]] that enables customers to update and recover their mobile device [[firmware]]<ref>http://europe.nokia.com/support/download-software/device-software-update</ref> of a recent [[Nokia Series 40|Series 40]] or [[S60 platform|S60]] device from any [[Internet]] enabled access point.
The full list of [http://europe.nokia.com/get-support-and-software/download-software/device-software-update/download supported phones] is available in the official site.
Nokia Software Updater beta phase has ended at August 25, 2011. NSU 3.0.495 has now been released to consumers. It can be downloaded from [http://betalabs.nokia.com/apps/nokia-software-updater here].
==Criticism== The Nokia Software Updater requires at least 256MB of RAM to function. This can be a problem with older systems on which attempting to start the application results in an error message.{{Citation needed|reason=reliable source needed|date=March 2011}} The Nokia Software Updater cannot be used behind authenticating proxies, making it fail in many corporate environments.{{Citation needed|reason=reliable source needed|date=March 2011}}
== Similar Nokia programs == === Nokia Download!=== Nokia Download! is a desktop application for downloading content to your mobile phone.<ref>http://nokiaexperts.com/nokias-download-utility-drives-crazy-app-free/</ref>
